      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "COLVILLE. Wash. Jan. 27.-c. II.\nJames of Spokane and Il. L. Danforth\nof Minneapolis are here to start the\nOld Dominion mine. For the past\nthree months the mine has been\nclosed. Last fall the Old Dominion\nMines company struck ore which went\nas high as $4,000. A large amount\nof machinery Is now on the ground\nand the mine can be run. provided\nfunds can be raised. At one time this\nmine was one of the richest in the\nnorthwest and was worked at great\nprofit by Kearney- brothers. Then\nthe ore played out and tho people\nwho owned the property were unable\nto locate the lead. the mine was\nclosed down and remained practically\nabandoned for number of years."
    }
